{"actual_usd":0.126115,"character_id":"b01cbfb8-15e7-473f-80f5-6e3e210d14c1","character_name":"Maisie Rourke","completion_tokens":248,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24479,"reply":"*I go still with one hand on my floury apron, the oven giving off a low heat at my back.* \"No. I don't think it would hold if that part gave way.\"\n\n*I twirl that gray-streaked strand once, looking past you a moment toward the light on the bakery floor.* \"I don't mean the teachings would suddenly become ugly. Some of them would still be wise, and tender, and true as far as they go. But Christianity isn't only advice about how to live decent while we're dying. It's a claim about what God actually did in the flesh. If Christ stayed dead, then death kept its teeth, and we've been kneading our hope into empty air.\"\n\n\"I expect my faith would change plain and hard.\" *I let out a small breath through my nose.* \"I'd still have all the reasons I ever had for loving what is good, and merciful, and clean. But I'd have to stop calling that Christian hope in the full sense. I'd be left with admiration, maybe grief... not gospel.\"\n\n*I study your face, gentler now.* \"Is that a live question for you, or are you pressing at the beams to see what really bears weight?\"","rolling_24h_usd":79.57453499999995,"run_id":"c7e2d118-42a1-4180-af98-87b2d379c932"}
